definition: king or monarch/best or strongest of its type/grand/great

sentences.english: Your ruling planet Mercury will encounter transforming Pluto this morning from your astrological money sector.
sentences.chinese: 今天上午你的主星水星會刑你的財帛宮冥王。

sentences.english: Atlas: I have woken the torment of the underworld, vanished to the darkest pit of Hades .
sentences.chinese: 我喚醒了地獄中的痛苦，在冥王最黑暗的深淵中隱去。

sentences.english: 1930 - The planet Pluto is officially named.
sentences.chinese: 1930年的今天，冥王星被正式命名。

sentences.english: If Pluto was a planet, Eris obviously was too.
sentences.chinese: 如果冥王星是行星，厄里斯星就也該是。

sentences.english: Pluto has a moon, called Charon, which is about the size of Quaoar itself.
sentences.chinese: 冥王星有一顆衛星，叫卡戎，和誇歐爾差不多大。

sentences.english: Pluto is now considered a dwarf planet dwelling in the Kuiper belt.
sentences.chinese: 冥王星現在被認定爲一顆處於柯伊伯帶中的矮行星。

sentences.english: Composite Pluto in the seventh house can have two quite opposite effects.
sentences.chinese: 合圖中，冥王星位於第七宮會產生兩種很不同的影響。

sentences.english: Pluto's discovery was a stone with its waves.
sentences.chinese: 冥王星的發現一石激起千層浪。

sentences.english: And whereas Pluto has an atmosphere, Charon apparently does not.
sentences.chinese: 冥王星有大氣層，冥衛一顯然就沒有。

sentences.english: In that draw lots , he became a night king.
sentences.chinese: 在那次抽籤中，他成爲了冥王。

sentences.english: This is either Nott or the Death Eater Luna Reducto-ed Pluto at.
sentences.chinese: 他是諾特或當面被盧娜擊碎冥王星的食死徒。

sentences.english: The full moon will be conjunct Pluto, indicating quite a powerful force.
sentences.chinese: 這次的滿月將會聯合冥王星，展示充滿的能量。

sentences.english: The Q is - do you mean Pluto in its aphelion or perihelion ?
sentences.chinese: 我的問題是，冥王星此時是在近地點還是遠地點？

sentences.english: It is all because, compared with Neptune, Pluto is very small.
sentences.chinese: 冥王星與海衛一幾乎同樣大小，同樣密度。

sentences.english: Pluto's orbit the Sun is 248 years.
sentences.chinese: 冥王星的軌道太陽是248年。

sentences.english: Pluto has family in the outer solar system.
sentences.chinese: 冥王星在太陽系外宇宙有着它自己的家族。

variant of 羅睺|罗睺[luo2 hou2]
Poseidon, Greek god of the sea/Neptune, Roman god of the sea/Aquaman, DC comic book superhero
the Yellow Springs/the underworld of Chinese mythology/the equivalent of Hades or Hell
Poseidon, God of the sea in Greek mythology
the intersection of the Moon's orbit with the ecliptic in Vedic astronomy (Sanskrit rahu)
